MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 364c2b772391e46dba637935c558b9b2, type: 3}
  m_Name: Gargoyle
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::MythSO
  pageNumber: 151
  mythName: Gargoyle
  omens:
  - '1. Two boisterous lads clamber on a ruined

    temple, smashing the eroded
    statuary

    with a heavy hammer. They say they''re

    just following orders
    from a nearby Seer.'
  - '2. The Gargoyle descends on the Company,

    shouting that he means no harm.
    He''s

    looking for a lost item, and expects the

    Knights to find it.
    He will cause an

    argument for his own amusement if he

    can, otherwise
    he leaves.'
  - '3. Atop a huge stone ruin, the Gargoyle

    carves away at the stone with his
    bare

    hands, sculpting beasts. Two such beasts

    watch on, eager for a
    new companion.'
  - '4. In the shade of a grey tree the Gargoyle

    argues with a nearby Seer.
    He claims that

    he alone gives the Seers their knowledge.

    This is a
    lie.'
  - '5. The two lads who were smashing statues

    lie petrified by a sculpted beast''s
    bite.'
  - '6. In a quarry the Gargoyle smashes his

    sculpted beasts to rubble one by
    one. They

    don''t resist. After this he takes flight for

    another Realm,
    declaring this one dull.'
  verse: 'In hearthy glow, small joys take flight

    Whilst bitter past doth dwell
    in spite'
  castEntries:
  - name: The Gargoyle, Astergrist
    statBlock: 'VIG 14, CLA 17, SPI 12, 6 GD

      A4 (hulking stony body), clumsy
      flight'
    notes: 'Great claws (2d8) and tail (d10 blast)

      Well-read and ill-tempered.
      Hates the sun.

      Wants to bring back anything old.

      Always seeking
      a specific item (see below).'
  - name: Sculpted Beast
    statBlock: 'VIG 10, CLA 6, SPI 6, 3 GD

      A3 (stony body, wolflike)'
    notes: 'Stone bite (2d8, wounds cause the victim to

      slowly petrify over
      the next week, reversed

      only if the Gargoyle grants a pardon)

      Mindlessly
      serves the Gargoyle''s whims.'
  flavorTable:
    title: LOST ITEM
    columns:
    - header: Object
      values:
      - Twisted tin flute
      - Bejewelled chess set
      - Huge cauldron
      - Map-marked shield
      - Mummified Seer head
      - Crown of raw iron
    - header: Last Seen
      values:
      - Sinking into water
      - In the Seat of Power
      - Seized by a Seer
      - Buried in the woods
      - Hurled from a peak
      - Entombed in a tree
  visibleByDefault: 0
  visibleMarkerPrefab: {fileID: 0}
